5 Sec. 1. 29 V.S.A. § 165 is amended to read:
6 § 165. SPACE ALLOCATION, INVENTORY, AND USE; LEASING
7 PROPERTY; COMMISSIONER’S PREAPPROVAL REQUIRED
8 * * *
9 (e) The Commissioner of Buildings and General Services shall maintain an
10 inventory of all State-owned or State-leased buildings and land and shall
11 biannually compile and update the information received under subsection (g)
12 of this section, which shall be considered once available in making spacing
13 allocations and designating uses under subsection (c) of this section.
14 * * *
15 (g) The head of each agency shall prepare and forward to the
16 Commissioner of Buildings and General Services when requested by the
17 Commissioner annually in a format prescribed by the Commissioner an
18 inventory of: square footage available for use; square footage in actual use;
19 square footage not in use; square footage used for storage; square footage that
20 is unfinished; cost per square foot for rent; cost per square foot for operation
21 and maintenance; and the source of funds for rent, operation, and maintenance,
